(859, 1, '2016-07-24 16:39:06', '2016-07-24 10:39:06', '<span id="one:_t136" class="black_light1">Pokhara Valley is the second-largest valley in the hilly region of Nepal. It lies in the western part of the Nepal. The cities of Pokhara and Lekhnath are in the valley. It is located in the Gandaki zone, 203 kilometres (126 mi) west of Kathmandu Valley.[1] The city of Pokhara is one of the major cities of Nepal, and like Kathmandu Valley, is extremely vulnerable to earthquakes due to its clay soil and liquefaction potential.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Package Includes :</strong>\r\n•     Return Air tickets by US Bangla with taxes\r\n•     Airport - Hotel - Hotel Transfer (SIC)\r\n•     Kathmandu – Pokhara – Kathmandu by AC bus with lunch\r\n•     Pokhra Bus stand - hotel - Pokhra Bus stand transfer by Car\r\n<strong>Package Excludes :</strong>\r\n•     Lunch, Dinner\r\n•     Which is not mention in includes\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Hotel Information:</strong>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.bd-tours.com/s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/70mmtours/images/in_hotel/hotel_kantipur.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="100" />\r\n<table cellpadding="10px">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td valign="top"><span class="h5"><span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:_t228">Hotel The Kantipur / Similar</span></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td valign="top"><span class="h5">Star Rating:</span> <img src="http://www.bd-tours.com/staticResources/filled_star.jpg" alt="" width="18" height="18" /> <img src="http://www.bd-tours.com/staticResources/filled_star.jpg" alt="" width="18" height="18" /> <img src="http://www.bd-tours.com/staticResources/filled_star.jpg" alt="" width="18" height="18" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top"><span class="h5"> Address:</span></td>\r\n<td><span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt233:0:_t235" class="black_light1">Hotel The Kantipur</span><span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt233:0:_t238" class="black_light1">, Pokhara</span><span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt233:0:_t239" class="black_light1">, Nepal</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td valign="top"><span class="h5"> Hotel Description: </span>\r\n<span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:_t243" class="black_light1">Kantipur is the poetic name of ancient Kathmandu the capital city of Nepal. Now, this poetic essence although disappearing in Kathmandu, has finally materialized in Pokhara 200 km all the way west of Kathmandu along with the combination of beauty, comfort and taste. That is in the class from of an exotic place to relax and enjoy delicious cuisine amidst the magnificent views of the most beautiful Himalaya "Fish Tail" of Annapurna range reflecting itself within the PHEWA LAKE. The hotel expertise started a decade ago from Kathmandu, promises to provide very special services which, we believe, will meet your every expectation required to make your stay memorable in the natural bowl of Pokhara Valley.</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td valign="top"><span class="h5">Features Characteristics:</span>\r\n•      <span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt245:0:_t247" class="black_light1">Bar/Lounge.</span>\r\n•      <span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt245:1:_t247" class="black_light1">Business Centre.</span>\r\n•      <span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt245:2:_t247" class="black_light1">Car parking.</span>\r\n•      <span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt245:3:_t247" class="black_light1">Doctor on call.</span>\r\n•      <span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt245:4:_t247" class="black_light1">Restaurant.</span>\r\n•      <span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt245:5:_t247" class="black_light1">Room service.</span>\r\n•      <span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt245:6:_t247" class="black_light1">Hot / cold water.</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<strong>About Destination:</strong>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.bd-tours.com/s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/70mmtours/images/int_destination/david_falls3.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Devi''s Fall pokhara</strong>\r\n\r\nThis is the famous waterfall of Pokhara called Devi''s Fall. Water coming from Phewa lake vanishes into the earth at the Devi''s Fall. Locally known as Patale Chhango, Devi''s fall is an attractive waterfall lying about 2 km south-west of Pokhara valley. Devi, a Swiss lady, was swept away when the floodgates were accidently opened.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.bd-tours.com/s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/70mmtours/images/int_destination/gupteswar_cave1.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Gupteswar Cave Pokhara</strong>\r\n\r\nThis cave is the significant cave of pokhara.it is also the main place for tourist attraction.the cave is divided into 2 parts .the first one is 40metre long.it is the main natural cave .here we can see the temple of lord shiva.to visit only this place we need to pay 30rupees.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.bd-tours.com/s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/70mmtours/images/int_destination/seti_river1.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Seti River Pokhara</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Seti Gandaki River, also known as the Seti River or the Seti Khola, is a river of western Nepal, a left tributary of the Trishuli River. It is one of the holiest rivers of Nepal, worshipped in Hinduism as a form of Vishnu. The river is also famous because it is close to some Holy places and is the central point of many stories of Hindu mythology, such as the Mahabharata, one of longest books of Hinduism, written by Vyasa, who was born near the confluence of the Gandaki and Madi rivers near Damauli, Tanahun, Nepal.', 'Kathmandu & Pokhra Tour Package (05 Days 04 nights)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kathmandu-pokhra-tour-package-05-days-04-nights', '', '', '2016-08-02 17:24:27', '2016-08-02 11:24:27', '', 0, 'http://ghuri.online/?post_type=tour&#038;p=859', 0, 'tour', '', 0),
