(868, 1, '2016-08-09 23:11:08', '2016-08-09 17:11:08', '<span id="one:_t136" class="black_light1">Kuala Lumpur is the capital of Malaysia. Kuala Lumpur has many interesting attractions; like Merdeka Square, Chinatown, Petronas Twin Towers and much more.\r\nPenang is a Malaysian island off the Malay Peninsula in the Malacca Strait. In George Town, the capital of Penang state, foreign influences are evident in landmarks such as colonial-era Fort Cornwallis, Chinese clan temple Khoo Kongsi and Indian-style Kapitan Keling Mosque.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Package Includes :</strong>\r\n•     Return Air Tickets of DAC - KUL - PEN - KUL - DAC by Malindo Air\r\n•     Airport - Kuala Lumpur Hotel - Penang Hotel - Airport transfer (SIC)\r\n•     02 nights double sharing accommodation at Kuala Lumpur Hotel Sentral Pudu, Sky Express &amp; Soleil 3* or Similar Hotel\r\n•     02 nights double sharing accommodation at Hotel Bay View / Gogre Town / Flamigo 3* or Similar Hotel, Penang\r\n\r\n<strong>Package Excludes :</strong>\r\n•     Visa Fees &amp; service charge per person BDT 4,500/-\r\n•     Lunch, Dinner\r\n•     Which is not mention in includes\r\n\r\n<strong>Hotel Information:</strong>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.bd-tours.com/s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/70mmtours/images/in_hotel/bayview.jpg" alt="" width="149" height="100" />\r\n<table cellpadding="10px">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td valign="top"><span class="h5"><span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:_t228">Hotel Bay View / Similar</span></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td valign="top"><span class="h5">Star Rating:</span> <img src="http://www.bd-tours.com/staticResources/filled_star.jpg" alt="" width="18" height="18" /> <img src="http://www.bd-tours.com/staticResources/filled_star.jpg" alt="" width="18" height="18" /> <img src="http://www.bd-tours.com/staticResources/filled_star.jpg" alt="" width="18" height="18" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top"><span class="h5"> Address:</span></td>\r\n<td><span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt233:0:_t235" class="black_light1">Hotel Bay View</span><span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt233:0:_t238" class="black_light1">, Penang</span><span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt233:0:_t239" class="black_light1">, Malaysia</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td valign="top"><span class="h5"> Hotel Description: </span>\r\n<span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:_t243" class="black_light1">Bayview Hotel Langkawi is located in the heart of the commercial district of downtown Kuah, which is a mere 5 minutes from the jetty where ferry boats ply to and from the mainland, and only 25 minutes from the airport.</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td valign="top"><span class="h5">Features Characteristics:</span>\r\n• <span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt245:0:_t247" class="black_light1">Bar/Lounge.</span>\r\n• <span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt245:1:_t247" class="black_light1">Business Centre.</span>\r\n• <span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt245:2:_t247" class="black_light1">Car parking.</span>\r\n• <span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt245:3:_t247" class="black_light1">Doctor on call.</span>\r\n• <span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt245:4:_t247" class="black_light1">Restaurant.</span>\r\n• <span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt245:5:_t247" class="black_light1">Room service.</span>\r\n• <span id="one:j_idt221:0:j_idt223:1:j_idt245:6:_t247" class="black_light1">Hot / cold water.</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<strong>About Destination:</strong>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.bd-tours.com/s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/70mmtours/images/int_destination/eagle1.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<strong><span class="h5"><span id="one:j_idt311:1:j_idt313:5:_t317">Eagle Square Penang</span></span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span id="one:j_idt311:1:j_idt313:5:_t319" class="black_light1">Eagle Square is the place that reflects origin of Penang''s name. The square is marked by a massive 12-meter sculpture of a reddish brown eagle which is poised to take off. Penang''s name has been derived from reddish brown eagle, because in old Malay language Helang means Eagle, and Kawi stands for reddish brown.</span>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.bd-tours.com/s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/70mmtours/images/int_destination/sky_bridge1.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<strong><span class="h5"><span id="one:j_idt311:1:j_idt313:6:_t317">Sky Bridge Penang</span></span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span id="one:j_idt311:1:j_idt313:6:_t319" class="black_light1">Penang Sky Bridge is a 125 meters curved pedestrian cable-stayed bridge, located at the peak of Gunung Mat Chinchang mountain, on Pulau Penang, an island in the Penang archipelago in Kedah, Malay</span>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.bd-tours.com/s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/70mmtours/images/int_destination/hip_hop1.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<strong><span class="h5"><span id="one:j_idt311:1:j_idt313:17:_t317">Around the Penang Tour</span></span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span id="one:j_idt311:1:j_idt313:17:_t319" class="black_light1">Penang, on Northwestern shore of Malaysia is a archipelago of Penang Islands. Situated Just where the Indian Ocean narrows down into the Straits of Melaka,it was once a heaven for pirates. Today it serves as a retreat for visitors near and far.</span>', 'Kuala Lumpur & Penang Tour ( 05 Days 04 Nights )', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kuala-lumpur-penang-tour-package-05-days-04-nights', '', '', '2016-08-10 01:36:03', '2016-08-09 19:36:03', '', 0, 'http://ghuri.online/?post_type=tour&#038;p=868', 0, 'tour', '', 0),
